.TH "buildgear build" 1 "<===DATE===>" "<===VERSION===>" "Buildgear"


.SH NAME
buildgear build \- Start buildgear build process.

.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBbuildgear build\fR [\fB\-\-keep-work\fR] [\fB\-\-update-checksum\fR]
                [\fB\-\-update-footprint\fR] [\fB\-\-no-strip\fR]
                [\fB\-\-no-fakeroot\fR] [\fB\-\-all\fR] <\fIpackage\fR>

.SH DESCRIPTION
The build command starts a the build process. If the \fB\-\-all\fR option is used, all packages in the current buildgear environment will be builed. If <\fIpackage\fR> is specified, a build of the package and all its dependencies is started.

The build sysroot is located in build/work

.SH OPTIONS

.TP
.B "--all"
.RS
Apply options to all build dependencies.
.RE

.TP
.B "--keep-work"
.RS
Do not delete the work files after a successfull build.
.RE

.TP
.B "--update-checksum"
.RS
Update source checksum.
.RE

.TP
.B "--update-footprint"
.RS
Update the package footprint.
.RE

.TP
.B "--no-strip"
.RS
Do not strip libraries and executables.
.RE

.TP
.B "--no-fakeroot"
.RS
Do not use fakeroot in the build process.
.RE

.SH CONFIG
The build behavior can be configured in the buildgear config file (See \fBbuildgear.config(7)\fR).

.TP
.B parallel_builds
.RS
The number of parallel building threads. The default is 1.
.RE

